# P/Invoke Patterns

## Randomized Namespace

The `mJiggAPI` namespace is randomized at startup (e.g. `ns_a3f7c019b2e84d01`). Never use `[mJiggAPI.Mouse]::` directly. Use script-scoped variables:

- `$script:MouseAPI` — Mouse class (GetCursorPos, SetCursorPos, GetAsyncKeyState, GetLastInputInfo, etc.)
- `$script:KeyboardAPI` — Keyboard class (keybd_event)
- `$script:ToastAPI` — Toast class (WinRT COM interop)
- `$script:PointType`, `$script:LastInputType`, `$script:InputRecordType`, `$script:CSBIType` — string type names for `New-Object`

## Marshal.SizeOf Gotcha (.NET Core)

Never pass a type to `[Marshal]::SizeOf()`. Always pass an already-created struct instance:
```powershell
$lii = New-Object $script:LastInputType
$lii.cbSize = [uint32][System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal]::SizeOf($lii)  # instance, not type
```

## Resize Detection

Use `GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo` on **stdout** handle (`GetStdHandle(-11)`), read `srWindow` directly. Never rely on `$Host.UI.RawUI.WindowSize` or `[Console]::WindowWidth` in polling loops — they return stale values.

## GetAsyncKeyState

- Bit 15 (0x8000) = key is currently down
- Bit 0 (0x0001) = key was pressed since last call (consumed on read, check once)
- Only used for mouse buttons (VK 0x01-0x06) and modifier keys

## VK_RMENU (165) Console Input Gotcha

`keybd_event` injects VK_RMENU (0xA5=165), but the console input layer reports it as VK_MENU (18). Always filter both 18 and 165 (plus all modifier VKs 16, 160-165).

## WinRT Toast COM

- Vtable order in `[ComImport]` interfaces must exactly match WinRT IDL — wrong order causes `AccessViolationException`
- Use `WindowsCreateString`/`WindowsDeleteString` for HSTRINGs — `UnmanagedType.HString` is broken in .NET 6+ P/Invoke
- Types cannot be unloaded once loaded via `Add-Type` — users must restart PowerShell session after C# type changes
